bake

public java.util.concurrent.Future<java.lang.Boolean> bake(BoundName productName,
                                                           com.google.common.collect.ImmutableList<BoundName> prereqs)
Returns a promise to bring the named product up-to-date.

Parameters:
prereqs - the products that this product depends on. We use these instead of the ingredient postReqs since the prereqs are guaranteed to be complete, while the postReqs for a Recipe depend on the products to be baked, and so are a subset of the dependers.
Returns:
a future whose result is true if the product is up-to-date, and false if it cannot be brought up-to-date.
